parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag failed to deploy in a crash
the driver or passenger suffered injuries due to the lack of airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts to repair the Takata airbag recall can lead to a prolonged period of risk for drivers and passengers, as the faulty airbags may still be in use.
symptoms: Receipt of multiple recall notices
inability to schedule repair due to parts unavailability
lack of communication from manufacturer or dealer regarding repair timeline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can lead to the airbag failing to deploy in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag sensor failed
the vehicle was not repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal assembly can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate while shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates while shifting gears
the vehicle jerks or lurches while shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission computer module can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, hesitation, or slipping while shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission malfunctions
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission slips or hesitates while shifting gears
the vehicle makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate while shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.

the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission slips or hesitates while shifting gears
the vehicle makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently without warning
the brake pedal is depressed to the floor but the vehicle fails to respond

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning indicator can indicate a faulty airbag system, which can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning indicator illuminates
unknown wires need to be replaced
the failure continues after repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the battery terminals can cause the battery to drain, leading to unexpected stalling or failure to start, which can result in accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The positive terminal of the car battery is loose

the vehicle dies while driving
the car will not start on the first try.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights just stop working
hitting a bump in the road turns them back on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can result in serious injury or death, as well as property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire
the car horn is stuck on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system malfunctions can cause unexpected stalling or failure to start, which can result in accidents or strand the driver.

the vehicle dies while driving
